UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2458
1 AN ACT relating to county jails.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 441.225 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) Except for capital improvements, utilities and building insurance and except as
5 provided in subsection (2) of this section, the jailer shall have authority to authorize
6 expenditures from the jail budget. These[Such] expenditures shall only be made in
7 accordance with the line item jail budget duly adopted or amended by the fiscal
8 court and the established county procurement code or purchase order procedure of
9 the county. Payment for purchases for the jail shall be subject to fiscal court
10 approval prior to payment. The fiscal court shall not withhold approval of payment
11 for jail expenditures which are within the jail budget and not unlawful.
12 (2) The jailer shall submit, in accordance with county payroll procedures, time reports
13 for all full-time and part-time jail personnel and employees to the county treasurer
14 or other designated payroll official. The county treasurer shall review and pay
15 those[such] claims in accordance with policies and procedures for the payment of
16 other county employees.
